      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercial CFD solver with documented QA processes and version control meets Gradation 1 requirements for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2 was used under institutional license with version-controlled case files. Solver release notes and known-issue logs were reviewed; no open defects affect the hemolysis shear-stress QoI. QA documentation is on file."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes standard benchmark verification test for rotating-frame flows at Gradation 1.",
      "rationale": "The Navier-Stokes solver was verified against the analytical Couette-flow and lid-driven cavity benchmarks. Computed velocities agreed with analytical solutions to within 0.8% across all tested Reynolds numbers, confirming correct code implementation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI below 5% for primary QoI (volume-averaged shear stress) across all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Three systematically refined meshes (4.2 M, 8.7 M, 17.1 M cells) were generated using consistent refinement ratio r = 1.26. GCI values for volume-averaged shear stress ranged from 1.4% to 2.9% across all five operating points, satisfying the 5% threshold. The fine-mesh solution was used for all reported RHI values."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions replicate the five CFD operating points within ±5% for flow rate and rotational speed.",
      "rationale": "Bench tests were conducted at the five flow-speed combinations (2 L/min–3500 RPM through 6 L/min–2500 RPM). Measured flow rates agreed with targets within ±2.1% and rotational speeds within ±0.8%, confirming adequate fidelity of the experimental boundary conditions relative to the CFD inputs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted RHI values within ±15% of experimentally measured RHI at all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted RHI values were compared against bench-measured plasma-free hemoglobin at each operating point. Prediction errors ranged from −9.4% to +11.7%, all within the ±15% acceptance criterion. The model consistently identified the 2 L/min–3500 RPM condition as worst-case, in agreement with experiment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (RHI derived from volume-averaged shear stress and exposure time) is directly linked to the clinical hemolysis endpoint for CPB.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index is a recognized surrogate for erythrocyte damage in CPB devices and is explicitly referenced in FDA guidance on blood-contacting device computational modeling. The power-law hemolysis model parameters were calibrated against published in-vitro data for human red blood cells, confirming direct relevance to the clinical endpoint."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments use the same device geometry, fluid (bovine blood or equivalent), and operating envelope as the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments were performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under the identical five operating points specified in the COU. Bovine blood with hematocrit 33±2% was used, consistent with CPB clinical practice. Geometric fidelity was confirmed by coordinate-measuring machine inspection of the physical test article against the CAD model."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence to residuals below 1×10⁻⁵ for all transport equations at each operating point.",
      "rationale": "All simulations were run to mass, momentum, and turbulence residuals below 1×10⁻⁵. Torque and outlet pressure monitors were tracked over the final 500 iterations and showed variation below 0.1%, confirming iterative convergence independent of discretization error."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor; scoping review confirms no unusual operator-driven model configuration risk.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, Gradation 1 for use error requires only that simulation inputs be reviewed by a second analyst. A peer review of boundary condition setup and material property assignments was completed; no discrepancies were found. Formal use-error analysis beyond peer review is not required at this risk level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; model form selection is documented and consistent with published hemolysis CFD literature.",
      "rationale": "The k-ω SST turbulence model and power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger coefficients) are the dominant choices in peer-reviewed CFD hemolysis literature for centrifugal pumps. Model form selection is documented in the simulation plan. Formal model-form uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; input parameters are sourced from published material data and device specifications.",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity, density, and hemolysis model coefficients are drawn from published sources with documented uncertainty ranges. Pump geometry inputs were derived from the FDA-released CAD model. Sensitivity of RHI to ±10% variation in viscosity was evaluated informally and found to produce less than 3% change in predicted RHI, supporting adequacy of nominal input values."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; a single representative test article is acceptable for validation at this risk level.",
      "rationale": "One physical pump specimen fabricated to nominal dimensions was used for all bench validation tests. At MRL 2, sample-to-sample variability characterization is not required. The specimen was inspected and confirmed to be within manufacturing tolerances prior to testing."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; boundary conditions in simulation and experiment are matched at the nominal level.",
      "rationale": "CFD boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, outlet pressure, rotational speed, fluid properties) were set to match measured experimental conditions at each operating point. Equivalency at the nominal level is confirmed by the test condition factor assessment. Formal equivalency analysis beyond nominal matching is not required at MRL 2."
